## Token Architecture

<!-- WHY: Explain the two-layer token system: primitives and semantics. -->
<!-- WHY: This helps buyers understand WHY tokens are named as they are. -->

This system uses a two-layer token architecture:

**Layer 1 ã Primitive Tokens:** Raw values with scale-based names.
Example: `brand-500: oklch(55% 0.22 250)`

**Layer 2 ã Semantic Tokens:** Named by role, referencing primitives.
Example: `primary: $brand-500`

Always use semantic tokens in application code. Primitive tokens exist only
to define the palette; semantic tokens carry meaning and adapt to themes.

**Naming convention:** `kebab-case` for all tokens.

