## Export Instructions

<!-- WHY: How to use this design system in a real project. -->
<!-- WHY: Be specific with file names and import syntax. -->

### Available Exports

| Format | File | Use For |
|--------|------|---------|
| Tailwind CSS | `exports/tailwind.config.js` | Tailwind-based projects |
| CSS Variables | `exports/css-variables.css` | Vanilla CSS / non-Tailwind |
| DTCG JSON | `exports/dtcg.json` | Design tool integration |

### Tailwind Installation

1. Copy `exports/tailwind.config.js` to your project root
2. Import in your entry CSS file:
   ```css
   @import './exports/css-variables.css';
   ```
3. Extend your existing Tailwind config or replace it entirely

### Using Tokens in Claude Code

When asking Claude Code to build UI with this design system:
```
Use the {{DESIGN_SYSTEM_NAME}} design system.
Reference tokens/colors.yaml for colors, tokens/typography.yaml for text.
Always use semantic tokens (e.g., `primary` not `brand-500`).
```

